President Trump hosted faith leaders in the White House and thanked them for their role in the nation's spiritual life. Vice President Pence also expressed gratitude for their support and highlighted the importance of prayer in American history. President Trump emphasized the renewal of religious liberty in America and announced that he would sign an executive order to check abuses of the Johnson Amendment, which prevents non-profit organizations, including churches, from engaging in political activity. The President assured the faith leaders that his administration would defend religious liberty for all citizens.